1
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:15,960
I'm sorry, gods!

2
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,190
The person on my mind has changed since last time,

3
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:20,190
so I've come to ask again.

4
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:23,500
My chances may be really low, but...

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:33,010
Kinda feels like something scandalous happened while those two were all alone.

6
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,880
But I'll do everything I can!

7
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:43,520
And so I ask for your favor!

8
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,910
It's hopeless.

9
00:00:52,910 --> 00:00:55,780
It's popped up in my memory every day since then.

10
00:00:57,330 --> 00:00:59,590
If Akari-chan isn't special to you,

11
00:00:59,590 --> 00:01:01,010
then will you show me...

12
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:04,060
a part of you that

13
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,150
Akari-chan doesn't know?

14
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:11,740
Why did I do that?

15
00:01:11,740 --> 00:01:15,300
I'm so glad summer break started right after that!

16
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:20,550
I panicked. I know that.

17
00:01:20,930 --> 00:01:24,640
My first was you...

18
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:27,210
but was it different for you?

19
00:01:27,700 --> 00:01:30,940
Um... Well, I mean...

20
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,500
Before that kiss with me in the nurse's office, Jiro-kun had already...

21
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:41,450
I didn't want to know...

22
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:43,080
But it's easy to tell.

23
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:50,580
Jiro-kun's wife is Akari-chan...

24
00:01:51,020 --> 00:01:54,390
So does that mean I'm just his childhood friend?

25
00:01:54,390 --> 00:01:57,240
That's awful. It's like I'm someone he had an affair with.

26
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,700
Jiro-kun...

27
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,480
What were you feeling when you kissed me?

28
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,650
I...

29
00:02:14,870 --> 00:02:15,990
Jiro-kun...

30
00:02:16,820 --> 00:02:22,690
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

31
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,800
It's criminal to be so shy

32
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:37,660
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

33
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:39,970
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

34
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:43,250
No less than supreme

35
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:46,660
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

36
00:02:47,550 --> 00:02:49,270
The wild ringing of bells

37
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:56,380
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

38
00:02:57,140 --> 00:03:00,060
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

39
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:05,610
A daydream that seems like fiction

40
00:03:05,610 --> 00:03:08,650
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

41
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:11,070
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

42
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:13,690
My heart hurts and hurts,

43
00:03:13,690 --> 00:03:18,580
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

44
00:03:18,580 --> 00:03:22,060
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

45
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:24,380
Be brave, my darling

46
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:26,960
It won't all be happy and fun

47
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,980
It's all up to us

48
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:31,190
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

49
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:34,840
Please look my way, darling

50
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:43,940
Please notice my pure love for you

51
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:52,290
Crap. What am I supposed to do?

52
00:03:52,290 --> 00:03:53,540
Now that it's come to this...

53
00:03:52,290 --> 00:03:55,540
Chloris

54
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,540
there's only one thing to do.

55
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:55,540
Take this!

56
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,800
Huh? What is that?

57
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,050
Chloris
I'm sorry.
Wha?!

58
00:03:59,050 --> 00:04:01,550
Chloris has kissed the Hero.

59
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:03,720
I'm so sorry!

60
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:11,060
Once we grow up, being childhood friends won't be enough to keep me by your side.

61
00:04:17,890 --> 00:04:20,570
Is it that moment with Shiori again?

62
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:23,720
In that moment, Shiori kissed me...

63
00:04:24,770 --> 00:04:27,240
And it didn't seem like she hated it.

64
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:30,270
To be honest, I felt like it was the only chance I'd get...

65
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:35,380
Like the first love I'd half given up on might bloom in that moment.

66
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:40,010
But afterward, Shiori apologized over and over,

67
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:42,590
and then she only said, "Let's head back."

68
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:45,150
What was she feeling?

69
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:47,480
Why did she kiss me and then apologize?

70
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:49,680
And anyway, that kind of thing...

71
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:53,900
First you fall in love and confess, then you start going out, hold hands...

72
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,820
Shouldn't it come after all that?

73
00:04:56,760 --> 00:05:00,930
What did she mean when she said being childhood friends wasn't enough to stay close?

74
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:03,500
What am I supposed to do?

75
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:08,410
If I had more EXP built up, I'd probably be able to come up with an answer, but...

76
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,900
No matter how much I think about it, I have no idea!

77
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:15,560
I think I'll go buy some cola, potato chips, and manga for now.

78
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:17,830
Jiro has run away.

79
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:27,840
Young Ace
An Ideal Life as a Sponging Boyfriend
Special Bonus Item 2
Bungo Stray Dogs Special Clear File Folder

80
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,710
This manga is already out?

81
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,060
Oh, excuse me!

82
00:05:29,060 --> 00:05:30,350
I'm sorry!

83
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:32,260
What?!

84
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:36,850
I-I never thought we'd meet in a place like this.

85
00:05:36,850 --> 00:05:38,870
Y-Yes, indeed.

86
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:41,360
Why are you being so formal?

87
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:44,830
I was just so surprised...

88
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:48,610
Wait, so... you read manga?

89
00:05:49,210 --> 00:05:52,670
No, I went to the shop next door to buy notebooks,

90
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:54,700
and my little brother asked me to get this.

91
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:57,370
Little brother... You mean Kenta?

92
00:05:57,370 --> 00:06:00,030
Yeah. He's been wanting to see you.

93
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:02,160
What? He remembers me?

94
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:05,130
Yeah. Since I've mentioned you, he's been wondering about you.

95
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,160
You... talk about me?

96
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:11,140
Oh, it looks like this is the last copy.

97
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:12,680
Here, you take it.

98
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,260
Huh? I couldn't!

99
00:06:14,670 --> 00:06:18,880
It's okay. I was gonna go shopping after this, anyway.

100
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,520
You can buy it and take it home.

101
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:23,520
You really are kind.

102
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,530
Huh? Did you say something?

103
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:27,660
No, nothing.

104
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,200
Thank you.

105
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:31,680
What a relief!

106
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,760
It was probably better to talk like this today

107
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,290
than starting out the new term with things still awkward.

108
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,480
Whoa, are you serious?

109
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,020
I think it's just a passing summer shower, but...

110
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:44,290
I didn't think it would rain.

111
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,960
You don't have an umbrella?

112
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:50,800
No. Maybe I'll buy one somewhere nearby.

113
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:57,960
"Well, I'll see you next term." Is that what I say now?

114
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,780
Is this where this event ends?

115
00:07:00,780 --> 00:07:04,160
Isn't this actually a chance to cement some future plans?

116
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:06,170
But then again...

117
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:09,320
Oh, come on! Say something, me!

118
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:15,020
Um, do you want to come to my place?

119
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:16,580
The one at the training dorm?

120
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:17,360
Huh?

121
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,690
It's nearby.

122
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:22,890
And I'd like to talk some more until the rain lets up.

123
00:07:22,890 --> 00:07:24,070
What do you think?

124
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:25,090
Are you sure?

125
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:28,330
S-Since this was so sudden, I don't have anything prepared,

126
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:30,210
but since I got the chance to see you...

127
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:33,590
Only if you have time, though.

128
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:38,350
Th-Thank you for inviting me over.

129
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,140
Hang on just a minute.

130
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:45,370
I want to make sure it isn't too messy.

131
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,320
My hands are sweating like crazy!

132
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:52,300
I hope I don't smell sweaty...

133
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:57,120
Welcome home, darling.

134
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,140
Huh?

135
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:02,040
J-Just kidding!

136
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:05,630
Sorry for doing that out of nowhere. Well, please, come on in!

137
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:08,630
Th-Thank you for having me.

138
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:19,640
The place is pretty stark, isn't it?

139
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:22,020
There's nothing at all in here.

140
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:24,120
My place is the same way!

141
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:27,020
And all the furniture's the same, so I kinda feel at home.

142
00:08:27,020 --> 00:08:29,120
May I sit next to you?

143
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,910
O-Of course! It's your place, after all.

144
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,360
It smells amazing.

145
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,160
What?!

146
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:46,220
Is this, y'know, quality stuff?

147
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:51,500
Oh, uh... Y-Yes, it's pretty much the real deal.

148
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,170
Wow, really?

149
00:08:53,170 --> 00:08:54,730
Just what I'd expect from you!

150
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:59,040
Of course he meant the coffee!

151
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,930
I'm such an idiot!

152
00:09:13,170 --> 00:09:14,950
I am way too happy right now!

153
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:18,970
I haven't taken in a single word of this manga,

154
00:09:18,970 --> 00:09:20,950
but I don't even care!

155
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,360
Her outfit is so demure...

156
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,210
She's so cute!

157
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:28,950
Her skin is so pale, and her wrists are so slender.

158
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:30,710
And she smells nice.

159
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:33,170
She's slim and dainty, but she seems soft, too.

160
00:09:33,930 --> 00:09:35,600
And her eyelashes are so long...

161
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:41,210
Um... Does something about me look weird?

162
00:09:41,210 --> 00:09:44,680
N-No... I was just wondering what you're reading.

163
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:48,480
Oh, this? It's a novel called Hello Summer, Goodbye.

164
00:09:48,890 --> 00:09:51,290
It's really good. I'll lend it to you sometime.

165
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:52,500
Th-Thanks.

166
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,750
I-I'm just going to go...

167
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,990
S-Sure.

168
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:02,300
When our eyes met, I didn't know what to do.

169
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:05,790
Maybe it was too pushy of me to invite him over after all.

170
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,730
Was he bored?

171
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:12,500
Or maybe he couldn't bring himself to say he wanted to leave?

172
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,890
What if he hates me now?

173
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:19,680
Does she hate me now?

174
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:22,510
Is she fed up because I don't know how to take the lead?

175
00:10:25,930 --> 00:10:28,520
But I mean... It's just...

176
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:31,560
I'm alone in a room with a girl who kissed me!

177
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,370
It'd be impossible not to be overly conscious of her!

178
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:41,690
Shiori isn't the type to be that assertive with just anyone.

179
00:10:41,690 --> 00:10:43,610
So the fact that she kissed me...

180
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:46,320
I'm allowed to be a little happy about that, right?

181
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:50,170
Maybe we do need to have a good talk about what happened that day...

182
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:51,520
Jiro-kun!
Yes?

183
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,110
Look outside!

184
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:53,920
Huh?

185
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,290
Whoa!

186
00:10:56,290 --> 00:10:58,120
It's a double rainbow!

187
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:00,940
That's so cool!

188
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:04,680
I've never seen anything like it before! It's beautiful!

189
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:07,680
Oh, I know!

190
00:11:08,050 --> 00:11:10,510
I'll get a shot with the rainbow. You get in it, too!

191
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:12,190
Huh? Y-You sure?

192
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,560
Okay! I'm taking it!

193
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:17,480
It looks great!

194
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:20,640
Double rainbows bring happiness.

195
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:23,160
I hope something nice happens.

196
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:25,750
Could you send that to me, too?

197
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:26,700
Of course!

198
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,130
Thanks.

199
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:29,710
Let's see...

200
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:32,460
Is it... now?

201
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,360
If I'm going to take a step, is now the time?

202
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,460
Um, I...

203
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,850
Look. You're in this one, too!

204
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:42,470
I'll send it at the same time.

205
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:47,050
It's the one we took at the beach. I really love this photo.

206
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:48,970
Everyone looks so happy.

207
00:11:55,980 --> 00:11:59,600
Oh, right. Were you about to say something?

208
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,420
Huh? Oh...

209
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:04,460
Uh, never mind. I forgot what it was.

210
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:07,620
The beach was fun, wasn't it?

211
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:08,540
Yeah!

212
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:15,750
I've been running from romance and that kind of thing all this time.

213
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:17,600
Which feeling is friendship?

214
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,520
Where does love start?

215
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:24,580
They're my own feelings, but at some point, I couldn't understand them anymore.

216
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:32,520
Why did I decide not to say anything in that moment?

217
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:37,670
Getting to a good place with Shiori was my dream, and yet...

218
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,190
It's probably just Kamo.

219
00:12:41,190 --> 00:12:44,170
Sorry, but I'm in no mood to deal with you.

220
00:12:45,470 --> 00:12:47,580
Oh, for crying out loud, what do you want?!

221
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:49,530
Message Just Now Watanabe Akari sent a sticker. 7 more messages
Akari?!

222
00:12:49,530 --> 00:12:52,040
P O P
Jiro
P O P
That was a shock.

223
00:12:51,470 --> 00:12:53,340
It's been half a month...
Yes, what is it?

224
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,210
Yes, what is it?
Jiro

225
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:56,040
Yes, what is it?
Jiro
I'm bored

226
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:57,580
My heart!

227
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:59,330
No! Don't give me that, heart!

228
00:12:59,330 --> 00:13:01,550
I bet she's sent that to a bunch of people.

229
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,550
Yes, what is it?
Jiro
I'm bored

230
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:04,050
Jiro
I'm bored
So am I

231
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:08,640
Ugh, I hate this!

232
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,640
Why am I so nervous?

233
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,560
It's just Jiro!

234
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:20,150
Then we'll meet in front of Seishun Station in 2 hours!

235
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,570
It's a date♥︎
Then we'll meet in front of Seishun Station in 2 hours!

236
00:13:21,570 --> 00:13:23,070
What?!

237
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:25,970
During summer break? Me and Akari?

238
00:13:25,970 --> 00:13:28,300
Points for the practical aren't being counted right now!

239
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,840
There's nothing in it for her, right?

240
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,790
What kind of trap is this?

241
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:34,690
Up until now, the two of us have only ever gone out to do regular errands, like shopping!

242
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:36,310
That way next!

243
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:37,370
She's not gonna make me buy her a ton of clothes, is she?

244
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:39,190
Virgin-kun, you seriously came here?

245
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,800
Or maybe it's not even that! She might just be messing with me!

246
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:40,800
That's hilarious! It was just a joke!

247
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,130
Sorry! I didn't think you'd take me seriously.
That's it! That's gotta be it!

248
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:51,640
It's a date♥︎

249
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:47,930
But supposing she's actually serious,

250
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:51,640
and she really is inviting me out, just as friends, of course...

251
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:53,320
Should I decline?

252
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,850
I just told her I was bored, though.

253
00:13:55,850 --> 00:13:59,150
I don't have anything I can wear to walk around with a gyaru!

254
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:03,400
Ten minutes early, huh?

255
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:06,000
A plain white T-shirt should be a safe choice, right?

256
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,240
I saw that written on an aggregator site, so...

257
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:10,320
Seriously, is someone out there waiting or something?

258
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,640
And is Akari really going to come?

259
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:13,910
It's nearly time.

260
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:17,120
Jeez, she didn't even show up.

261
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,170
I mean, I knew it was coming, but...

262
00:14:19,170 --> 00:14:21,170
15 minutes later

263
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,200
Guess I'll go home.
Jiro!

264
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:25,680
I'm so glad you're still here!

265
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:28,170
It took longer than I thought to get ready.

266
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,000
I ran out in a rush.

267
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,230
Then, after I got to the station, I realized I'd forgotten my phone.

268
00:14:33,230 --> 00:14:34,680
I'm super sorry!

269
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,360
Jiro, are you angry?

270
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:41,080
Huh? Uh, no, I'm not.

271
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,380
I didn't think you'd really come, anyway.

272
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:44,440
What?!

273
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,400
What does that mean?

274
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,440
S-Sorry!

275
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:50,670
Um, it's just that we don't usually do stuff like this with just us two,

276
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:52,530
so I guess I just couldn't imagine it.

277
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:55,450
But... I told you it was a date, didn't I?

278
00:14:55,450 --> 00:14:59,160
After all the effort I put in to get ready, there's no way I wouldn't show up.

279
00:15:00,220 --> 00:15:01,120
Hey...

280
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:02,580
Do I look cute?

281
00:15:04,610 --> 00:15:06,060
You have nothing to say?

282
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:09,680
I-It's not like the stuff you usually wear, so it's new and different!

283
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:10,340
And?

284
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:15,720
Um, I think clothes like the ones you're wearing today... are really nice.

285
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,060
Thanks. That makes me really happy.

286
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:20,800
Because this outfit is just for you.

287
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:21,480
Huh?

288
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:25,440
You said before that you liked things like this, right?

289
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:29,360
So... It's not the kind of thing I'd normally wear,

290
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,990
so buying it was a first for me.

291
00:15:30,990 --> 00:15:32,240
What?

292
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,790
Huh? Why?

293
00:15:33,790 --> 00:15:35,450
She wanted it to suit my tastes?

294
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,190
Huh?

295
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,690
Okay, let's go!

296
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,880
I have a ton of places I wanna go today!

297
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,500
Come with me to all of them, okay?

298
00:15:45,970 --> 00:15:49,010
Wha... What is even going on here?!

299
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:54,260
Which one should I get?

300
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:55,960
Have you decided what you're getting?

301
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:58,640
No... I don't even know which way is up right now.

302
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:00,300
Then you should get this one.

303
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:02,590
I seriously have no idea.

304
00:16:02,590 --> 00:16:04,900
Why is Akari doing this with me?

305
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:07,620
I bet you didn't know about this café, right?

306
00:16:07,620 --> 00:16:10,830
I'd heard of it. We saw it on TV together.

307
00:16:10,830 --> 00:16:13,150
You said it was a favorite of yours.

308
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:16,010
You remembered.

309
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:18,590
And now it's your momentous Ex-choco debut.

310
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:20,660
Drink up! Hurry!

311
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:22,950
Like it?

312
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:24,840
Yeah! Even more than I imagined!

313
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:27,240
Really? But isn't it bitter?

314
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,790
There is some bitterness, but it's good.

315
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:30,860
Let me taste it!

316
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:31,420
Huh?

317
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:34,300
I can't? You're so stingy.

318
00:16:34,770 --> 00:16:35,610
Go ahead.

319
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:42,680
Ugh! You liar! It's super bitter!

320
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,130
I know that face.

321
00:16:44,130 --> 00:16:46,310
You're thinking, "That was an indirect kiss," aren't you?

322
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,360
No... er, yes, I am.

323
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:51,550
Jeez, stop getting all embarrassed over stuff like that.

324
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:53,860
It makes me feel embarrassed, too.

325
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:55,360
Huh?

326
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:59,010
Has Akari always been like this?

327
00:16:59,490 --> 00:17:01,830
They're so cute!

328
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:05,080
Oh, wow! They really are just lying around everywhere!
They're just too cute!

329
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:08,590
They really are used to this! How cute!

330
00:17:08,590 --> 00:17:11,820
I'm used to seeing Akari smile like this now,

331
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:13,430
There, there.

332
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:15,160
but I never would've imagined it based on my first impression of her.

333
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:17,600
If we hadn't been a married couple,

334
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,850
I'd probably never have known this side of her.
Here?

335
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:22,850
You're such a good kitty.

336
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:25,850
Oh, it's so cute!

337
00:17:26,230 --> 00:17:28,440
That's all you've said since we got here.

338
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:30,580
Yeah, because my dearest wish has come true!

339
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:32,570
Here, Jiro! Try petting it!

340
00:17:32,570 --> 00:17:33,840
It's really soft!

341
00:17:34,410 --> 00:17:35,100
See?

342
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,360
You're right!

343
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:37,570
Meow.

344
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:44,870
Playing games through the night every day is the real thrill of summer break,

345
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:49,190
but it might be okay to have days like this sometimes, too.

346
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:51,040
That's what I found myself thinking.

347
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,330
I'll send you that picture in the chat, okay?

348
00:17:55,330 --> 00:17:57,150
Sure. Thanks.

349
00:17:57,150 --> 00:17:58,890
Oh! I'll send this, too.

350
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,880
A picture from the cat café.

351
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:03,390
Ack! When did someone take that?

352
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:06,890
The lady said, "I'm taking your picture now."

353
00:18:06,890 --> 00:18:08,920
I didn't notice at all.

354
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,400
Plus, this picture looks sort of like...

355
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,130
a family photo, doesn't it?

356
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:15,590
Huh?

357
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:19,400
I mean, it might be because of the way it was taken, but...

358
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,400
It's like the cat is the baby, and...

359
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:25,500
I-I-I was just thinking that some family photos look like that, is all!

360
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,540
She must be so creeped out!

361
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:29,770
That's hilarious! What the heck?

362
00:18:29,770 --> 00:18:32,040
Huh? She isn't creeped out?

363
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:35,000
It'd be nice if we could keep it as a pet during our practical.

364
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,400
I guess... it would.

365
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:40,050
Let's go to the cat café together again. I'll invite you.

366
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:45,430
Pedestrian Crossing Signal
Could it be that she invited me because she actually wanted to hang out with me?

367
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:48,220
You said yours is the upstairs ticket gate, right?

368
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:50,170
That's right. What about you?

369
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,430
I'm taking the subway.

370
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:53,690
What? Oh, sorry! We already passed that!

371
00:18:53,690 --> 00:18:55,720
Don't be! It's really close.

372
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,640
This kinda feels weird, doesn't it?

373
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,850
We usually go home to the same place,

374
00:19:00,850 --> 00:19:03,700
but this time we're saying goodbye and going to different places.

375
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:04,450
Yeah.

376
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:08,450
But... that's going to happen eventually, isn't it?

377
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:10,670
I might feel a little lonely.

378
00:19:10,670 --> 00:19:12,110
Just kidding! Oh!

379
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:12,490
Huh?

380
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:15,430
I forgot to buy a charm at the shrine!

381
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:17,660
A charm? What kind?

382
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:19,560
I-I'll tell you later!

383
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,300
Huh? Hey, Akari!

384
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:25,470
Hey, wait up! Akari!

385
00:19:27,370 --> 00:19:29,980
Jiro-kun? And Watanabe-san, too?

386
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,490
Shiori?

387
00:19:31,490 --> 00:19:33,120
Sakurazaka-san?

388
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:35,120
What a coincidence. Were you shopping?

389
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,790
You're carrying a lot.

390
00:19:36,790 --> 00:19:38,990
Yeah. You two, too?

391
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:43,290
That's right. I figured he'd be holed up in his room without me around,

392
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,870
so I thought I'd get him a little sunlight.

393
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,850
I see. Are you on your way home now?

394
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:51,760
Yeah. I just have something to do at the shrine.

395
00:19:53,710 --> 00:19:57,010
Watanabe-san, do you remember that we met at the shrine in the spring?

396
00:19:57,010 --> 00:19:57,880
Oh, yeah.

397
00:19:58,310 --> 00:20:01,880
I was just about to go pay my respects there.

398
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:08,150
Can I go, too? Want to race?

399
00:20:08,150 --> 00:20:10,390
Huh? What? Race?

400
00:20:11,790 --> 00:20:14,150
Sure. Let's do it! No holding back!

401
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:15,530
What?!

402
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,450
Okay, then, Jiro...

403
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:18,880
Huh? Wai—

404
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,220
Would you?
Hang on! Hey!

405
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:29,900
Ready...

406
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,620
Go!

407
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,140
Here!
Got it!

408
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:41,980
Watanabe-san, you're really fast!

409
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,870
You're not bad yourself, Sakurazaka-san!

410
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:47,990
Oh, my. What's happened here?

411
00:21:47,990 --> 00:21:50,330
Are you girls all right?

412
00:21:50,990 --> 00:21:55,250
I'm sorry we worried you. We were just racing each other, that's all.

413
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:58,150
Oh, is that so? You gave us a fright.

414
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,750
Didn't they, Jiro-san?

415
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,310
Yes, they did.

416
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:06,760
Jiro?

417
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:10,440
Come, now. If you don't pay attention, you'll trip and fall.

418
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:11,760
Right.

419
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:12,550
Honestly...

420
00:22:12,550 --> 00:22:14,520
He does seem a little like Jiro.

421
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,520
Come on.

422
00:22:14,910 --> 00:22:16,420
He really does.

423
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,780
I have no idea what's going on.

424
00:22:31,230 --> 00:22:33,280
Now, really put your hearts into it!

425
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:34,830
Right!

426
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,810
This place is famous for fulfilling romantic wishes, isn't it?

427
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:45,670
I...

428
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:40,560
Thanks! I'll handle the rest myself.

429
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,520
Okay, thanks.

430
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:49,280
Akari! I'll help make dinner!

431
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:52,030
Jiro has leveled up! He has gone with Lancia and Chloris to face their next adventure.

432
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:53,530
This looks tasty!

433
00:23:53,530 --> 00:23:54,280
Right?

434
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:55,430
What're you writing with the ketchup tonight?

435
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:57,030
Love

436
00:23:55,430 --> 00:23:57,030
Hmm, what shall I write?

437
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:57,620
Huh?
Let's see...

438
00:23:58,610 --> 00:23:59,180
Oh!

439
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,240
Hang on a sec.

440
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,400
This is...

441
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:03,460
Go like this, and then like this...

442
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:04,400
And it's done!

443
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,420
Ack!

444
00:24:05,420 --> 00:24:07,250
Your special omelet rice.

445
00:24:05,420 --> 00:24:09,960
2nd
Miyajidake Asahi Najima Nanako
3rd
Tenjin Minami Sakurazaka Shiori
4th
Yakuin Jiro Watanabe Akari
Okubo Osamu Shuto Kyoko

446
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,570
Are you serious?

